---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { APPS, SEGMENTS, USE_CASES, description, pageTitle, siteFromHost } from '../content';
const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '';
const title = pageTitle(site, path);
const desc = description(site, path);
const recommended = APPS.filter(a => a.channels.includes(site.channel) || a.channels.includes('marketing')).slice(0,10);
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path="/">
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#0b1028] py-20 text-white md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-90 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_10%_20%,#6366f1_0,transparent_28%),radial-gradient(circle_at_85%_15%,#c084fc_0,transparent_24%),linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1028,#111827_55%,#312e81)]"></div>
    <div class="container relative grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-end">
      <div>
        <span class="badge badge-dark">Calm catalog · broad Shopify email stack</span>
        <h1 class="hero-title mt-6 text-white">Shopify email tools for campaigns, flows, updates, and customer education</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-indigo-100">{site.heroPromise} This rebuilt site is deliberately broader than a retention-only directory: it covers practical email tools for newsletters, lifecycle automation, product education, customer updates, segmentation, deliverability, and the daily work of keeping a Shopify customer file useful.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Browse tools</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases">Explore use cases</a></div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="card dark-card"><div class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-200">Catalog rule</div><p class="mt-3 text-white">A Shopify email tool should reduce operational friction: faster sends, cleaner lists, clearer content blocks, and fewer manual exports.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark-card"><div class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-200">Buyer rule</div><p class="mt-3 text-white">{site.bestOverallReason}</p></div>
        <div class="card dark-card sm:col-span-2"><div class="text-sm font-black text-indigo-200">Scope</div><p class="mt-3 text-white">The pages below separate app reviews, alternatives, pairwise comparisons, store-type guides, and email jobs so merchants can choose tools by practical fit instead of copying another store's stack.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-16"><div class="mb-8 flex flex-col gap-3 md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between"><div><span class="badge">Tool shelf</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Email tools worth opening first</h2></div><a class="link" href="/apps">See all app profiles →</a></div><div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5">{recommended.map((app, i) => <a class="card compact-card" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}><div class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-700">Shelf {i+1}</div><h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-black text-slate-950">{app.name}</h3><p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">{app.bestFor}</p></a>)}</div></section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16"><div class="container"><div class="max-w-3xl"><span class="badge">Long-form map</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Built for merchants who need the right email job, not just the biggest suite.</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">A general Shopify email tool decision is different from a narrow email marketing platform decision. Some stores need a fast newsletter workflow. Others need product-triggered education, simple customer updates, lightweight automations, or a bridge toward a larger retention program. The content map treats these as separate jobs with separate evaluation criteria.</p></div><div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">{USE_CASES.slice(0,12).map(u=><a class="card" href={`/use-cases/${u.slug}`}><h3 class="font-black text-slate-950">{u.name}</h3><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">A practical guide to {u.job}.</p></a>)}</div></div></section>

  <section class="container py-16"><div class="mb-8"><span class="badge">Store contexts</span><h2 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Email tooling changes by catalog and customer behavior</h2></div><div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-4">{SEGMENTS.map(s=><a class="card" href={`/for/${s.slug}`}><h3 class="font-black">{s.name}</h3><p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Plan around {s.pain}.</p></a>)}</div></section>

  <section class="bg-[#0b1028] py-16 text-white">
    <div class="container grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[.9fr_1.1fr]">
      <div>
        <span class="badge badge-dark">Operating guide</span>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">How to choose a Shopify email tool without buying the wrong category of software.</h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-indigo-100">The mistake with broad Shopify email tooling is treating every product as if it is trying to solve the same job. A newsletter tool, a lifecycle automation platform, a template builder, a deliverability helper, and a retention operating system can all touch email, but they change the merchant’s day in very different ways. The best choice starts with the work your team needs to repeat every week.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-indigo-100">
        <p>If the team mostly sends product launches, editorial updates, and simple promotions, the key buying criteria are speed, reusable blocks, clean product insertion, list hygiene, and a reporting view that makes the next campaign obvious. A huge automation suite may look impressive but slow down a small team that only needs dependable campaign production.</p>
        <p>If the store is trying to build retention, the criteria change. The tool needs to understand first purchase timing, order count, product categories, replenishment windows, loyalty status, discount history, and the difference between a subscriber who browsed once and a customer who bought three times. Without that context, email becomes a broadcast channel instead of a customer system.</p>
        <p>For Shopify, the most useful email stack usually grows in layers: capture subscribers, welcome them, recover immediate intent, educate after purchase, time the second order, reactivate lapsing customers, and protect deliverability as volume increases. The right tool should make the current layer easier while not blocking the next one.</p>
        <p>Use this site as a working catalog rather than a logo directory. Open the app reviews for product fit, the comparison pages for tradeoffs, the use-case pages for workflow depth, and the store-type pages for category-specific pressure. A good tool should survive all four views before it earns a place in the stack.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
